00:16:16,975 --> 00:16:19,478
(Yui's voice) Did your father do something to you, Yamaguchi-san?

260
00:16:19,478 --> 00:16:22,981
My woman almost died because of Yagami's medicine!

261
00:16:22,981 --> 00:16:24,983
picture? (Yamaguchi) It's a great company.

262
00:16:24,983 --> 00:16:26,985
You're hiding it!

263
00:16:26,985 --> 00:16:29,485
So this guy has nothing to do with it. Ah?

264
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:35,494
You take the hostage and run away➡

265
00:16:35,494 --> 00:16:37,496
He started flirting with me and calling me "Hachirin".

266
00:16:37,496 --> 00:16:39,498
Don't get carried away! Not like that!

267
00:16:39,498 --> 00:16:42,501
It's as if you betrayed Saito!

268
00:16:42,501 --> 00:16:44,503
Why is that so?

269
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:46,505
Because of you, the old man became a criminal and died!

270
00:16:46,505 --> 00:16:48,507
Don't talk back!

271
00:16:48,507 --> 00:16:50,509
Hey! Hey! (Kicking sound)

272
00:16:50,509 --> 00:16:54,009
(Yamaguchi) Oh! Hey! Hey…! (Kicking sound)

273
00:16:57,015 --> 00:16:58,517
(Hosaka) In this trial, there was a person named Kenji Yamaguchi➡

274
00:16:58,517 --> 00:17:00,017
There is a record of him testifying.

275
00:17:12,030 --> 00:17:14,032
(Hosaka) He survived, but lost his eyesight due to the aftereffects➡

276
00:17:14,032 --> 00:17:16,034
Demanding damages of 100 million yen from Yagami Pharmaceutical➡

277
00:17:16,034 --> 00:17:18,036
I'm filing a lawsuit.

278
00:17:18,036 --> 00:17:22,541
Yamaguchi is on the witness stand as the woman's lover.

279
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:24,543
What was the result?

280
00:17:24,543 --> 00:17:26,545
No loss of vision➡

281
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:29,548
I realized that I was just pretending to be blind➡

282
00:17:29,548 --> 00:17:31,550
The suit was dismissed.

283
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:33,552
It's a mess, isn't it?

284
00:17:33,552 --> 00:17:36,555
Just to confirm, everything Yamaguchi said was a lie➡

285
00:17:36,555 --> 00:17:38,557
Is this a correct interpretation?

286
00:17:38,557 --> 00:17:40,058
no thanks.

287
00:17:40,058 --> 00:17:43,562
No other serious problems have been reported with the affected product➡

288
00:17:43,562 --> 00:17:46,064
It is still being sold today.

289
00:17:46,064 --> 00:17:49,067
What is your impression of Yamaguchi from your point of view?

290
00:17:49,067 --> 00:17:51,069
(Hosaka) I guess there are times.

291
00:17:51,069 --> 00:17:53,572
From the outside, there is no legitimacy➡

292
00:17:53,572 --> 00:17:56,074
I believe that the person who said it is right.

293
00:17:56,074 --> 00:17:58,577
That's why it's so bad.

294
00:17:58,577 --> 00:18:00,577
Because we can't communicate.

295
00:18:08,587 --> 00:18:16,595
Smartphone) (ring tone)

296
00:18:16,595 --> 00:18:18,597
Why don't you come out...? Smartphone) (ring tone)

297
00:18:18,597 --> 00:18:24,603
Smartphone) (ring tone)

298
00:18:24,603 --> 00:18:39,551
♬～

299
00:18:39,551 --> 00:18:42,554
(Smartphone) Dad, I'm sorry for worrying you.

300
00:18:42,554 --> 00:18:45,557
Smartphone) I don't remember much about it until now➡

301
00:18:45,557 --> 00:18:48,560
A kind person helped me.

302
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:50,560
Smartphone) I'm going home now.

303
00:18:55,067 --> 00:18:58,570
Smartphone) (vibrating sound)

304
00:18:58,570 --> 00:19:00,570
(Yamaguchi) Hello.

305
00:19:03,075 --> 00:19:06,078
Are you a “good guy with no money”?

306
00:19:06,078 --> 00:19:08,080
that's right.

307
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:10,582
Smartphone) Um... My name is Yagami.

308
00:19:10,582 --> 00:19:15,587
Ah, good, we're finally connected.

309
00:19:15,587 --> 00:19:19,091
Umm... Yui is okay, right?

310
00:19:19,091 --> 00:19:20,592
(Yamaguchi) Yeah.

311
00:19:20,592 --> 00:19:23,092
You seem a little tired though.

312
00:19:25,097 --> 00:19:28,600
Thank you. Can I speak to Yui?

313
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:42,547
♬～

314
00:19:42,547 --> 00:19:44,049
hello.

315
00:19:44,049 --> 00:19:46,551
Hello, is it Yui?

316
00:19:46,551 --> 00:19:48,553
Smartphone) Yes.

317
00:19:48,553 --> 00:19:50,555
good….

318
00:19:50,555 --> 00:19:52,055
Are you okay?

319
00:19:56,061 --> 00:19:59,064
Before I knew it, I was lying on the roadside➡

320
00:19:59,064 --> 00:20:01,566
This person helped me.

321
00:20:01,566 --> 00:20:03,568
Smartphone) Did it fall down?

322
00:20:03,568 --> 00:20:07,072
Isn't he with you?

323
00:20:07,072 --> 00:20:09,072
Smartphone) My name is Hayashida...

324
00:20:13,578 --> 00:20:16,081
That person is no longer with me.

325
00:20:16,081 --> 00:20:17,582
Smartphone) I see.

326
00:20:17,582 --> 00:20:21,082
Anyway, I'm glad you're safe. (Smartphone) Dad...

327
00:20:23,088 --> 00:20:26,091
Please thank this person properly.

328
00:20:26,091 --> 00:20:28,593
Because it's a lifesaver.

329
00:20:28,593 --> 00:20:30,593
Of course I know.

330
00:20:33,098 --> 00:20:37,035
Where are you? I'll come pick you up right away.

331
00:20:37,035 --> 00:20:38,537
father.

332
00:20:38,537 --> 00:20:40,539
If you find Yui, the reward will be 300 million yen➡

333
00:20:40,539 --> 00:20:43,041
...I posted it on the website, right?

334
00:20:43,041 --> 00:20:45,544
Ah yes.

335
00:20:45,544 --> 00:20:48,044
Smartphone) (Yamaguchi) Has your feeling changed?

336
00:20:50,048 --> 00:20:52,050
of course.

337
00:20:52,050 --> 00:20:54,553
If that's the case, why don't you take Yui-san with you➡

338
00:20:54,553 --> 00:20:56,555
Can I transfer the money on the spot?

339
00:20:56,555 --> 00:20:59,558
I understand, which one should I ask...

340
00:20:59,558 --> 00:21:02,060
(Yamaguchi) I'll take Yui to the office.

341
00:21:02,060 --> 00:21:04,062
Is it okay in 3 hours?

342
00:21:04,062 --> 00:21:06,064
Understood.

343
00:21:06,064 --> 00:21:08,066
I'll be waiting for you.

344
00:21:08,066 --> 00:21:10,566
See you later.

345
00:21:14,072 --> 00:21:16,074
Haha...

346
00:21:16,074 --> 00:21:18,076
Please release these two.

347
00:21:18,076 --> 00:21:21,079
One of these days. You don't feel like going back.

348
00:21:21,079 --> 00:21:24,583
I'll drop it somewhere conspicuous when I get to the airport.

349
00:21:24,583 --> 00:21:27,085
If I'm lucky, someone might be able to help me.

350
00:21:27,085 --> 00:21:30,088
Don't be silly! Does the airport allow you to escape overseas?

351
00:21:30,088 --> 00:21:34,025
It's not easy to live in a country like this.

352
00:21:36,027 --> 00:21:38,530
(Yamaguchi) Hey, stand up! Let's go.

353
00:21:38,530 --> 00:21:41,032
Hurry up and walk! Hey!

354
00:21:41,032 --> 00:21:55,032
♬～

355
00:21:58,051 --> 00:22:02,055
Why was that reporter talking about Yamaguchi just now?

356
00:22:02,055 --> 00:22:04,991
Did you call? Hahahahaha…! Wow! I was surprised!

357
00:22:04,991 --> 00:22:07,494
They probably installed a GPS without my knowledge, right?

358
00:22:07,494 --> 00:22:09,496
You came to Yagami Pharmaceutical earlier, right?

359
00:22:09,496 --> 00:22:10,997
I've been wearing it ever since then➡

360
00:22:10,997 --> 00:22:12,499
Didn't you notice?

361
00:22:12,499 --> 00:22:15,001
Do not follow detectives.

362
00:22:15,001 --> 00:22:17,504
I feel confident.

363
00:22:17,504 --> 00:22:19,506
(Tabata) Why did Mr. Shiraki choose Yamaguchi?

364
00:22:19,506 --> 00:22:21,508
Did you know that you were part of the kidnapper group?

365
00:22:21,508 --> 00:22:24,511
I heard from someone that you might want to hurry.

366
00:22:24,511 --> 00:22:26,511
You must have entered this store.

367
00:22:28,515 --> 00:22:31,017
I guess the kidnapping case isn't over yet.

368
00:22:31,017 --> 00:22:33,520
If I talk to you, can you give me information about Yamaguchi?

369
00:22:33,520 --> 00:22:36,523
Why would the police do something like that...Tabata.

370
00:22:36,523 --> 00:22:40,023
You, go smoke a cigarette. I don't want a cigarette...

371
00:22:42,028 --> 00:22:43,528
yes.

372
00:22:44,531 --> 00:22:47,531
Hurry up and don't be impatient!

373
00:22:51,538 --> 00:22:53,540
Ugh…｡

374
00:22:53,540 --> 00:22:55,540
Ah...｡

375
00:23:00,547 --> 00:23:02,549
thank you.

376
00:23:02,549 --> 00:23:04,984
Let's go...

377
00:23:04,984 --> 00:23:07,987
Hey….

378
00:23:07,987 --> 00:23:09,487
Ugh...!

379
00:23:11,491 --> 00:23:13,493
(Sound of stun gun) Argh...!

380
00:23:13,493 --> 00:23:21,000
♬～

381
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:23,000
Oh no.

382
00:23:28,007 --> 00:23:30,510
Oh, would you like one last thing?

383
00:23:30,510 --> 00:23:33,012
Why are you listening?

384
00:23:33,012 --> 00:23:35,014
Mr. Komiyama is Daisuke Hayashida➡

385
00:23:35,014 --> 00:23:37,514
Do you want to be arrested? Don't you want to?

386
00:23:40,019 --> 00:23:42,519
I want him to be rehabilitated properly.

387
00:23:44,023 --> 00:23:49,028
(Komiyama) Daisuke probably had that intention as well.

388
00:23:49,028 --> 00:23:51,528
But he also became involved in crime.

389
00:23:53,032 --> 00:23:55,535
If you really want to rehabilitate ➡

390
00:23:55,535 --> 00:23:58,037
Unless Daisuke himself wants to do that➡

391
00:23:58,037 --> 00:24:00,039
It's probably meaningless.

392
00:24:00,039 --> 00:24:04,043
For example, for someone important?

393
00:24:04,043 --> 00:24:06,980
I agree.

394
00:24:06,980 --> 00:24:10,480
There are limits to what you can do for yourself.

395
00:24:11,985 --> 00:24:14,988
Screen) (curl) We finally secured the majority of the shares.

396
00:24:14,988 --> 00:24:17,490
Screen) This is our victory.

397
00:24:17,490 --> 00:24:20,994
Screen) Congratulations, President Carl.

398
00:24:20,994 --> 00:24:22,495
Ha...!

399
00:24:22,495 --> 00:24:23,997
(Fuji) I will contact you later.

400
00:24:23,997 --> 00:24:25,999
Why aren't you answering the phone?

401
00:24:25,999 --> 00:24:28,001
Is your body okay?

402
00:24:28,001 --> 00:24:30,003
Anyway, I found the answer.

403
00:24:30,003 --> 00:24:33,003
Please prepare the 300 million reward money immediately.

404
00:24:35,008 --> 00:24:38,511
I'm sorry, but I don't have that authority. What?

405
00:24:38,511 --> 00:24:42,515
Please use your own money. Authority? What do you mean?

406
00:24:42,515 --> 00:24:45,018
Hoover Pharmaceuticals just said➡

407
00:24:45,018 --> 00:24:48,018
Acquired a majority stake in Yagami Pharmaceutical.

408
00:24:49,522 --> 00:24:51,022
Hoover?

409
00:24:53,526 --> 00:24:59,032
Does that mean Kyo-san sold his shares?

410
00:24:59,032 --> 00:25:01,032
yes.

411
00:25:02,535 --> 00:25:04,037
That's a lie...

412
00:25:04,037 --> 00:25:06,039
I can't help it. It's a lie!

413
00:25:06,039 --> 00:25:07,540
This is the reality.

414
00:25:07,540 --> 00:25:10,043
Shit...! Damn...!

415
00:25:10,043 --> 00:25:14,047
Ahhh!!

416
00:25:14,047 --> 00:25:16,547
Ah...!

417
00:25:22,555 --> 00:25:25,058
Why so much?

418
00:25:25,058 --> 00:25:27,558
I can stay calm.

419
00:25:30,063 --> 00:25:34,063
Thank you for your help so far.

420
00:25:37,570 --> 00:25:39,572
Fufufu…｡

421
00:25:39,572 --> 00:25:42,075
(cough cough)

422
00:25:42,075 --> 00:25:44,077
There are procedures for management transition➡

423
00:25:44,077 --> 00:25:47,077
It would be helpful if you could clean it up early.

424
00:25:49,082 --> 00:25:52,585
No way…➡

425
00:25:52,585 --> 00:25:54,087
With Hoover?

426
00:25:54,087 --> 00:25:55,588
yes.

427
00:25:55,588 --> 00:26:02,095
♬～

428
00:26:02,095 --> 00:26:04,097
Get out.

429
00:26:04,097 --> 00:26:06,032
It's already here➡

430
00:26:06,032 --> 00:26:09,535
It's not your room... Get out!

431
00:26:09,535 --> 00:26:11,537
Get out!!

432
00:26:11,537 --> 00:26:21,037
♬～

433
00:26:26,552 --> 00:26:29,055
Screen) Just a while ago, by Hoover Pharmaceuticals in the United States➡

434
00:26:29,055 --> 00:26:32,058
The acquisition of Yagami Pharmaceuticals has been officially decided.

435
00:26:32,058 --> 00:26:34,060
Screen) Yui Yagami's kidnapping ➡

436
00:26:34,060 --> 00:26:36,062
In a very serious situation... Smartphone) (notification sound)

437
00:26:36,062 --> 00:26:38,064
Screen) What will President Keishi Yagami do?➡

438
00:26:38,064 --> 00:26:40,066
There are also growing concerns on the ground.

439
00:26:40,066 --> 00:26:42,568
(Screen) President Yagami has not yet appeared.

440
00:26:42,568 --> 00:26:44,568
I wonder if it's finished.

441
00:26:49,575 --> 00:26:51,077
It's fine here.

442
00:26:51,077 --> 00:26:53,079
Wait a minute, don't drop me off here.

443
00:26:53,079 --> 00:26:55,081
There's a station right there. It's dangerous, isn't it?

444
00:26:55,081 --> 00:26:58,084
What will you do if that person finds you again?

445
00:26:58,084 --> 00:27:00,586
Could you please come to my aunt's villa?

446
00:27:00,586 --> 00:27:02,588
Eh, no, but...｡ It's my fault➡

447
00:27:02,588 --> 00:27:05,525
I'm really sorry for making you feel so bad.

448
00:27:05,525 --> 00:27:07,527
There is also a nice bath➡

449
00:27:07,527 --> 00:27:09,529
Please take it easy if you like.

450
00:27:09,529 --> 00:27:12,031
Is it okay? Of course.

451
00:27:12,031 --> 00:27:14,031
thank you.

452
00:27:15,034 --> 00:27:17,036
Hurry up!

453
00:27:17,036 --> 00:27:26,546
♬～

454
00:27:26,546 --> 00:27:28,548
Thank you.

455
00:27:28,548 --> 00:27:31,050
Did you find out? (Shiraki) Yeah.

456
00:27:31,050 --> 00:27:35,054
Yamaguchi seems like a very dangerous person.

457
00:27:35,054 --> 00:27:37,056
What about Yui and the others?

458
00:27:37,056 --> 00:27:40,059
It seems like I was able to escape for the time being.

459
00:27:40,059 --> 00:27:44,063
That's good... that's what I want to say➡

460
00:27:44,063 --> 00:27:47,563
It doesn't seem like he has the balls to give up.

461
00:27:53,072 --> 00:27:55,572
(Yamaguchi) Uh... ah...｡

462
00:27:57,076 --> 00:28:00,580
Shit...

463
00:28:00,580 --> 00:28:04,083
Who is this guy➡

464
00:28:04,083 --> 00:28:06,519
You're getting in my way...!

465
00:28:06,519 --> 00:28:08,019
Huh… hah…｡

466
00:28:11,022 --> 00:28:13,024
I'm back. Welcome back!

467
00:28:13,024 --> 00:28:15,026
This is Linda's mother.

468
00:28:15,026 --> 00:28:18,029
My name is Tomoko Hayashida, and I am sorry for the inconvenience caused to you and my son...

469
00:28:18,029 --> 00:28:21,029
No, I'm glad you're safe.

470
00:28:23,034 --> 00:28:24,536
I've just returned.

471
00:28:24,536 --> 00:28:28,039
What's wrong with that face? Isn't something getting worse and worse?

472
00:28:28,039 --> 00:28:29,541
It can't be helped.

473
00:28:29,541 --> 00:28:32,544
I'm sorry, it's unsightly... (Kyoto) That's outrageous!

474
00:28:32,544 --> 00:28:35,547
He protected the two of us, right?

475
00:28:35,547 --> 00:28:37,447
Well.

476
00:28:39,484 --> 00:28:40,984
Ite…｡

477
00:28:43,988 --> 00:28:45,990
Well, I used to have a lighter with me.

478
00:28:45,990 --> 00:28:48,990
Ah, give it back.

479
00:28:51,996 --> 00:28:54,999
This time, he saved me.

480
00:28:54,999 --> 00:28:57,001
Yes, Mickey gave it to me.

481
00:28:57,001 --> 00:28:59,504
A hamburger shop? Yeah.

482
00:28:59,504 --> 00:29:02,006
Is it something like this?

483
00:29:02,006 --> 00:29:05,009
Have you become handsome? Why don't you look in the mirror?

484
00:29:05,009 --> 00:29:07,512
picture?

485
00:29:07,512 --> 00:29:10,515
Mom wasn't a shitty old woman at all.

486
00:29:10,515 --> 00:29:14,018
teeth? He took care of Yamaguchi.

487
00:29:14,018 --> 00:29:17,522
Anyone would do that in that situation.

488
00:29:17,522 --> 00:29:19,522
I guess so...

489
00:29:21,025 --> 00:29:23,025
Don't be fooled.

490
00:29:24,529 --> 00:29:27,031
((Gambling melts away your money))

491
00:29:27,031 --> 00:29:29,033
((No way, I borrowed money from you right away➡

492
00:29:29,033 --> 00:29:31,033
Even I had to make money))

493
00:29:33,538 --> 00:29:35,540
(Tomoko's voice) Then please give my regards to the manager.

494
00:29:35,540 --> 00:29:39,978
Phone) (Colleague) Also, Mr. Hayashida, do you owe money to bad people?

495
00:29:39,978 --> 00:29:42,480
picture? Why?

496
00:29:42,480 --> 00:29:45,483
(Telephone) I came to work.

497
00:29:45,483 --> 00:29:47,485
Sorry for bothering you...

498
00:29:47,485 --> 00:29:49,988
I'll be going to work properly starting tomorrow.

499
00:29:49,988 --> 00:29:51,489
(Sound of call being disconnected)

500
00:29:51,489 --> 00:29:57,996
♬～

501
00:29:57,996 --> 00:30:00,498
thank you very much.

502
00:30:00,498 --> 00:30:02,998
What are you going to do now?

503
00:30:05,503 --> 00:30:09,007
My father thought I would come back➡

504
00:30:09,007 --> 00:30:12,010
I've got the money ready and waiting.

505
00:30:12,010 --> 00:30:15,010
What does Yui-chan want to do?

506
00:30:17,015 --> 00:30:21,519
I talked to my aunt yesterday➡

507
00:30:21,519 --> 00:30:24,522
What I felt about my father➡

508
00:30:24,522 --> 00:30:28,526
I thought it might have been a misunderstanding.

509
00:30:28,526 --> 00:30:34,032
Yes. But maybe not.

510
00:30:34,032 --> 00:30:38,469
So still...➡

511
00:30:38,469 --> 00:30:41,973
I'm scared to meet you.

512
00:30:41,973 --> 00:30:45,977
I guess that's fine then?

513
00:30:45,977 --> 00:30:48,479
Yui-chan did it herself➡

514
00:30:48,479 --> 00:30:53,479
I want to meet you. You can go see me whenever you want to talk.

515
00:30:55,987 --> 00:30:57,989
yes.

516
00:30:57,989 --> 00:31:01,492
Besides, it must be difficult for the company right now.

517
00:31:01,492 --> 00:31:02,994
Is that so?

518
00:31:02,994 --> 00:31:06,497
Yagami Pharmaceutical stocks that I owned➡

519
00:31:06,497 --> 00:31:09,500
I sold it to Hoover.

520
00:31:09,500 --> 00:31:12,503
If you sell it to Keishi, Keishi will be safe.

521
00:31:12,503 --> 00:31:17,008
If Keishi sells to Hoover, he will be forced out of Yagami Pharmaceutical.

522
00:31:17,008 --> 00:31:21,008
At such a fork in the road, I chose the latter.

523
00:31:24,015 --> 00:31:29,520
I also talked to Yui yesterday and thought about a lot of things.

524
00:31:29,520 --> 00:31:34,025
So I decided.

525
00:31:34,025 --> 00:31:43,925
♬～

526
00:31:47,972 --> 00:31:51,476
Hey Yui-chan. Yes.

527
00:31:51,476 --> 00:31:54,476
Can I talk to you for a while?

528
00:31:55,980 --> 00:31:57,482
500,000…｡

529
00:31:57,482 --> 00:32:01,986
Ah...but if I can borrow it, even 100,000 or 200,000 would be helpful.

530
00:32:01,986 --> 00:32:03,988
I'll definitely return it.

531
00:32:03,988 --> 00:32:06,991
Sorry, I don't have any money right now.

532
00:32:06,991 --> 00:32:11,496
Ah...then, uh...could I ask your aunt for something?

533
00:32:11,496 --> 00:32:14,999
I think you will be surprised if I suddenly ask you something like this➡

534
00:32:14,999 --> 00:32:19,504
But I would really appreciate it if you could borrow even a little bit.

535
00:32:19,504 --> 00:32:21,504
please.

536
00:32:23,007 --> 00:32:25,510
What are you doing?

537
00:32:25,510 --> 00:32:27,510
It's nothing.

538
00:32:29,514 --> 00:32:32,016
You were trying to borrow money, right?

539
00:32:32,016 --> 00:32:34,519
My mom is really having a hard time right now...

540
00:32:34,519 --> 00:32:36,521
Don't be silly.

541
00:32:36,521 --> 00:32:39,021
You must be gambling!

542
00:32:40,525 --> 00:32:44,028
I'm really sorry...but I have to return the money➡

543
00:32:44,028 --> 00:32:47,031
I might get fired from the company... That's abnormal.

544
00:32:47,031 --> 00:32:50,031
I'm about to borrow money from the bee I just met!

545
00:32:53,538 --> 00:32:56,038
Please be careful.

546
00:32:58,042 --> 00:33:00,542
Why is it always your fault...?

547
00:33:02,046 --> 00:33:06,050
What do you think my life is?

548
00:33:06,050 --> 00:33:08,050
Please give me a break...

549
00:33:13,558 --> 00:33:15,558
What is it? It's okay.

550
00:33:17,562 --> 00:33:21,566
I won't lend it to you. Don't ask me to lend it to you.

551
00:33:21,566 --> 00:33:23,566
Didn't you think so?

552
00:33:29,574 --> 00:33:32,076
Mother➡

553
00:33:32,076 --> 00:33:35,580
Maybe I have a gambling addiction.

554
00:33:35,580 --> 00:33:38,015
Addiction? Yeah.

555
00:33:38,015 --> 00:33:41,519
That's what happened to Mickey's younger brother.

556
00:33:41,519 --> 00:33:45,022
So I heard a lot of things...

557
00:33:45,022 --> 00:33:49,527
Huh... do you mean sick?

558
00:33:49,527 --> 00:33:52,530
He's not sick, that guy.

559
00:33:52,530 --> 00:33:55,032
When you become addicted➡

560
00:33:55,032 --> 00:33:58,035
I can't stop even if I want to.

561
00:33:58,035 --> 00:34:04,041
Contrary to my thoughts, I also hurt someone important to me➡

562
00:34:04,041 --> 00:34:06,541
It's really painful.

563
00:34:08,546 --> 00:34:11,549
So what should I do? First of all➡

564
00:34:11,549 --> 00:34:16,554
The person himself/herself thinks, “I want to change this life” ➡

565
00:34:16,554 --> 00:34:19,557
It seems to be the first step towards treatment.

566
00:34:19,557 --> 00:34:22,059
For that ➡

567
00:34:22,059 --> 00:34:26,063
It's no good to help halfway.

568
00:34:26,063 --> 00:34:28,065
Do you mean abandon me?

569
00:34:28,065 --> 00:34:30,067
That's different.

570
00:34:30,067 --> 00:34:42,013
♬～

571
00:34:42,013 --> 00:34:48,019
He gave birth to me when he was 20 years old➡

572
00:34:48,019 --> 00:34:52,023
I don't have a father, so please don't make me suffer ➡

573
00:34:52,023 --> 00:34:55,023
I know you worked hard.

574
00:34:58,529 --> 00:35:03,529
It's like having your parents participate in a sports day.

575
00:35:06,037 --> 00:35:11,542
That's why he ran the relay.

576
00:35:11,542 --> 00:35:14,542
Everyone else is my dad.

577
00:35:17,048 --> 00:35:23,054
But it's the fastest among them➡

578
00:35:23,054 --> 00:35:26,054
It was the coolest.

579
00:35:29,060 --> 00:35:31,560
But things have changed.

580
00:35:37,501 --> 00:35:40,001
Is Hachi's father the same?

581
00:35:42,506 --> 00:35:45,009
Even though it has changed ➡

582
00:35:45,009 --> 00:35:47,509
There's probably a reason.

583
00:35:51,515 --> 00:35:53,017
Is it my fault?

584
00:35:53,017 --> 00:35:55,017
Eh, why?

585
00:35:58,522 --> 00:36:02,026
It must have been difficult, right? Don't you raise it?

586
00:36:02,026 --> 00:36:04,028
But that's...

587
00:36:04,028 --> 00:36:08,532
Please don't make me feel pathetic.

588
00:36:08,532 --> 00:36:12,036
I suddenly felt a lot of pressure and got tired➡

589
00:36:12,036 --> 00:36:16,036
Like... addicted to gambling?

590
00:36:18,542 --> 00:36:21,045
It's not Linda's fault➡

591
00:36:21,045 --> 00:36:24,545
I don't think my mother became a bad person.

592
00:36:26,050 --> 00:36:28,552
Don't abandon me➡

593
00:36:28,552 --> 00:36:32,556
In order to change this situation even a little bit➡

594
00:36:32,556 --> 00:36:35,559
I think there are still things I can do➡

595
00:36:35,559 --> 00:36:36,959
What do you think?

596
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:45,000
Is there someone you would like to meet?

