00:37:39,991 --> 00:37:41,993
(knock)

610
00:37:41,993 --> 00:37:43,493
(Kyoto) ⚟Please⚞

611
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:52,503
Thank you for your help.

612
00:37:52,503 --> 00:37:54,003
home.

613
00:37:56,507 --> 00:37:59,510
In the end, it looks like he was able to escape safely on his own.

614
00:37:59,510 --> 00:38:01,012
That's right.

615
00:38:01,012 --> 00:38:04,515
But a promise is a promise.

616
00:38:04,515 --> 00:38:06,017
please.

617
00:38:06,017 --> 00:38:07,917
yes.

618
00:38:10,955 --> 00:38:13,458
Nice to meet you again➡

619
00:38:13,458 --> 00:38:16,961
My name is Shiraki from Weekly Shinryu.

620
00:38:16,961 --> 00:38:31,961
♬～

621
00:38:34,979 --> 00:38:42,979
I can hear the sound of white wood

622
00:38:44,989 --> 00:38:47,492
What color am I?

623
00:38:47,492 --> 00:38:49,994
I can't see the color.

624
00:38:49,994 --> 00:38:53,994
But I don't regret meeting you.

625
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:58,000
That would be great.

626
00:39:05,009 --> 00:39:07,909
Is the Yagami family really that interesting?

627
00:39:11,449 --> 00:39:13,951
Yeah.

628
00:39:13,951 --> 00:39:17,955
My life was changed by Chairman Kyoichi.

629
00:39:17,955 --> 00:39:19,957
what do you mean?

630
00:39:19,957 --> 00:39:23,461
I used to work as a reporter for a economic newspaper.

631
00:39:23,461 --> 00:39:26,464
When I interviewed Chairman Kyoichi there➡

632
00:39:26,464 --> 00:39:29,964
I was shocked and wondered, ``Who is this person?''

633
00:39:31,969 --> 00:39:34,472
Would you say I was fascinated?

634
00:39:34,472 --> 00:39:37,475
Was my father that strong?

635
00:39:37,475 --> 00:39:39,977
Yeah, there's no one else like him.

636
00:39:39,977 --> 00:39:42,980
What about me?

637
00:39:42,980 --> 00:39:45,983
Honestly…➡

638
00:39:45,983 --> 00:39:48,986
I felt something similar➡

639
00:39:48,986 --> 00:39:52,990
There was nothing strange or scary about it.

640
00:39:52,990 --> 00:39:55,993
Yes, that's good.

641
00:39:55,993 --> 00:39:57,995
When Chairman Kyoichi held my hand➡

642
00:39:57,995 --> 00:40:00,998
I thought my soul had been sucked out.

643
00:40:00,998 --> 00:40:05,503
(Kyoto) It didn't look like a monster. Yes, it was a monster.

644
00:40:05,503 --> 00:40:08,005
Ahhh.

645
00:40:08,005 --> 00:40:13,010
Mr. Shiraki was also chosen in a sense.

646
00:40:13,010 --> 00:40:15,012
Is it me?

647
00:40:15,012 --> 00:40:17,014
The side that was touched is ➡

648
00:40:17,014 --> 00:40:20,017
It seems like most of the time I don't feel anything.

649
00:40:20,017 --> 00:40:21,519
picture?

650
00:40:21,519 --> 00:40:24,019
I don't know which one is better though.

651
00:40:26,023 --> 00:40:28,023
I...

652
00:40:31,028 --> 00:40:34,031
I think it was good.

653
00:40:34,031 --> 00:40:36,534
Even though my father ruined my life?

654
00:40:36,534 --> 00:40:38,536
Yeah.

655
00:40:38,536 --> 00:40:40,536
Is that so...

656
00:40:42,039 --> 00:40:44,041
(Shiraki) It seems like there are other people who were selected just now➡

657
00:40:44,041 --> 00:40:46,041
You said it that way, right?

658
00:40:49,046 --> 00:40:51,046
Are you President Keishi?

659
00:40:53,050 --> 00:40:55,050
You have good intuition.

660
00:40:56,554 --> 00:40:58,556
(Tomoko) Your younger brother?

661
00:40:58,556 --> 00:41:00,057
(Tsboi) Yeah.

662
00:41:00,057 --> 00:41:05,057
(Tsboi) I didn't know it was that painful.

663
00:41:09,500 --> 00:41:11,502
I would also like to request it.

664
00:41:11,502 --> 00:41:14,502
Please start treatment.

665
00:41:16,007 --> 00:41:20,011
But what should I do...

666
00:41:20,011 --> 00:41:23,014
Gambling addicts gather ➡

667
00:41:23,014 --> 00:41:25,516
There are self-help groups.

668
00:41:25,516 --> 00:41:27,518
Self-help group...

669
00:41:27,518 --> 00:41:32,018
(Tsboi) First of all, please try to participate there.

670
00:41:33,524 --> 00:41:38,024
Um... could that be a cure?

671
00:41:40,531 --> 00:41:43,034
At first ➡

672
00:41:43,034 --> 00:41:47,538
You may think, ``I'm different from other people.''

673
00:41:47,538 --> 00:41:51,542
But while I was passing through➡

674
00:41:51,542 --> 00:41:55,546
You might start to think of them as friends.

675
00:41:55,546 --> 00:41:58,049
When I was talking with my friends➡

676
00:41:58,049 --> 00:42:02,553
What makes you gamble?

677
00:42:02,553 --> 00:42:05,556
Sometimes you can find it.

678
00:42:05,556 --> 00:42:08,993
When you can talk to people about your worries➡

679
00:42:08,993 --> 00:42:13,498
There's no need to cover up your hard feelings with gambling.

680
00:42:13,498 --> 00:42:16,000
Do it like that➡

681
00:42:16,000 --> 00:42:22,006
``I didn't have to do it today.'' ``I didn't do it today either.''

682
00:42:22,006 --> 00:42:25,510
Build up days like that.

683
00:42:25,510 --> 00:42:28,513
Does that mean it won't heal that quickly?

684
00:42:28,513 --> 00:42:31,015
(Tsboi) Yes.

685
00:42:31,015 --> 00:42:35,520
1 day 1 week 1 month ➡

686
00:42:35,520 --> 00:42:38,022
Half a year to 1 year.

687
00:42:38,022 --> 00:42:42,527
Make friends and work together➡

688
00:42:42,527 --> 00:42:44,527
I'm going to stop.

689
00:42:48,533 --> 00:42:52,033
You don't have to fight alone anymore.

690
00:42:56,040 --> 00:43:07,985
(cry)

691
00:43:07,985 --> 00:43:13,491
Can I... change?

692
00:43:13,491 --> 00:43:15,493
(cry)

693
00:43:15,493 --> 00:43:17,995
You can change.

694
00:43:17,995 --> 00:43:28,506
(cry)

695
00:43:28,506 --> 00:43:31,008
You too➡

696
00:43:31,008 --> 00:43:33,511
It was tough.

697
00:43:33,511 --> 00:43:44,522
♬～

698
00:43:44,522 --> 00:43:47,525
(Tomoko's voice) You met a nice person.

699
00:43:47,525 --> 00:43:52,025
Yui-chan has what Daisuke needs.

700
00:43:54,532 --> 00:43:58,035
When I’m with Hachi➡

701
00:43:58,035 --> 00:44:01,035
I feel like I shouldn't have thrown it away either.

702
00:44:03,541 --> 00:44:08,980
He's smart, but he's always acting like a nuisance➡

703
00:44:08,980 --> 00:44:11,983
Although it may be blurry ➡

704
00:44:11,983 --> 00:44:14,986
It's strong.

705
00:44:14,986 --> 00:44:18,486
I don't think it's bad anyway.

706
00:44:20,491 --> 00:44:22,493
Even if you feel stuck➡

707
00:44:22,493 --> 00:44:25,493
Are you trying to take even one step forward?

708
00:44:27,999 --> 00:44:31,502
When I see something like that➡

709
00:44:31,502 --> 00:44:34,502
I wonder if I can't do it yet.

710
00:44:38,009 --> 00:44:41,512
If I give up, things will never change ➡

711
00:44:41,512 --> 00:44:44,012
Maybe if I try, things will change.

712
00:44:46,517 --> 00:44:50,021
The chances of it changing are very low, though.

713
00:44:50,021 --> 00:44:52,523
But➡

714
00:44:52,523 --> 00:44:55,523
I thought I'd take a chance on that.

715
00:44:57,528 --> 00:45:03,028
I think I should try to believe that I too have a future.

716
00:45:06,037 --> 00:45:07,937
that's why….

717
00:45:10,975 --> 00:45:12,975
I'll turn myself in.

718
00:45:15,479 --> 00:45:17,479
I'll start my life over again.

719
00:45:21,986 --> 00:45:23,986
You should try again too.

720
00:45:26,991 --> 00:45:28,991
Yeah.

721
00:45:37,501 --> 00:45:40,001
It's from here.

722
00:45:42,506 --> 00:45:44,508
Mom too.

723
00:45:44,508 --> 00:45:56,020
♬～

724
00:45:56,020 --> 00:45:59,023
I was saved by a bee again.

725
00:45:59,023 --> 00:46:02,526
It's not like I helped you.

726
00:46:02,526 --> 00:46:04,528
I just did it because I wanted to.

727
00:46:04,528 --> 00:46:06,528
Don't try to be cool.

728
00:46:07,965 --> 00:46:10,968
But it was good.

729
00:46:10,968 --> 00:46:14,968
I still don't trust that damn old hag though.

730
00:46:16,474 --> 00:46:19,974
I don't even believe you, Dad.

731
00:46:21,979 --> 00:46:23,979
But I'll meet you.

732
00:46:26,484 --> 00:46:27,985
I see.

733
00:46:27,985 --> 00:46:30,985
I don't like feeling anxious all by myself.

734
00:46:32,490 --> 00:46:35,993
Tsukasa: Are you okay by yourself? Huh?

735
00:46:35,993 --> 00:46:40,498
I'm already going to turn myself in. It's okay, Dad, I'm weak right now.

736
00:46:40,498 --> 00:46:44,502
Scary, that's the reason. It's got to be a joke, right?

737
00:46:44,502 --> 00:46:46,502
What is it?

738
00:46:49,507 --> 00:46:52,510
As expected... I'll go with you.

739
00:46:52,510 --> 00:46:54,011
Why?

740
00:46:54,011 --> 00:46:56,514
"I'm sorry for having to drag you around until now."

741
00:46:56,514 --> 00:47:00,017
Are you there? That's it. That's it.

742
00:47:00,017 --> 00:47:03,020
I'm looking at the future.

743
00:47:03,020 --> 00:47:04,522
What is that?

744
00:47:04,522 --> 00:47:07,458
It's okay if you don't understand.

745
00:47:07,458 --> 00:47:09,960
So should I apologize to Linda's mother too?

746
00:47:09,960 --> 00:47:12,463
No need, bees don't apologize.

747
00:47:12,463 --> 00:47:14,465
I'm sorry for having to carry your son around until now.

748
00:47:14,465 --> 00:47:16,967
Wait, wait, wait, wait, what is this pointless conversation?

749
00:47:16,967 --> 00:47:18,469
It's the last one.

750
00:47:18,469 --> 00:47:21,469
Hachi is my second life, I'm a pig box.

751
00:47:23,474 --> 00:47:26,474
The last one... Ah.

752
00:47:29,480 --> 00:47:31,982
this.

753
00:47:31,982 --> 00:47:34,485
Will you keep it for me?

754
00:47:34,485 --> 00:47:35,986
I understand.

755
00:47:35,986 --> 00:47:37,488
What about Hachi?

756
00:47:37,488 --> 00:47:40,491
I put it in my bag before it disappeared.

757
00:47:40,491 --> 00:47:41,991
I see.

758
00:47:43,994 --> 00:47:45,996
But it won't be the last.

759
00:47:45,996 --> 00:47:47,498
picture?

760
00:47:47,498 --> 00:47:49,998
Are you going to come get this someday?

761
00:47:52,002 --> 00:47:53,504
That's right.

762
00:47:53,504 --> 00:48:07,952
♬～

763
00:48:07,952 --> 00:48:09,954
Even a kiss is fine.

764
00:48:09,954 --> 00:48:20,464
♬～

765
00:48:20,464 --> 00:48:22,464
I'll stop.

766
00:48:23,968 --> 00:48:25,968
Because it seems like it's the last time.

767
00:48:28,973 --> 00:48:30,473
That's right.

768
00:48:31,976 --> 00:48:33,477
Huh...

769
00:48:33,477 --> 00:48:35,479
(knock)

770
00:48:35,479 --> 00:48:37,979
